OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,FHousehold energy prices are expected
OL,7,Fto fall in July, according to a
OL,8,Fforecast ahead of the next energy
OL,9,Fprice cap update.
OL,11,FConsultancy Cornwall Insight predicts
OL,12,Fthe average UK customer will pay 7%
OL,13,Fless in energy bills from July to
OL,14,FOctober than under the current cap.
OL,16,FThe energy price cap, regulated by
OL,17,FOfgem, restricts the amount that
OL,18,Fenergy suppliers can charge for each
OL,19,Funit of gas and electricity and covers
OL,20,Faround two-thirds of homes in the UK.
