OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,FOfgem will release its updated energy
OL,7,Fprice cap, which will come into force
OL,8,Fin July, on May 27.
OL,10,FCornwall Insight estimates that
OL,11,Ffollowing April's increase in the
OL,12,Fenergy cap, prices will now continue
OL,13,Fto fall with a modest drop in October,
OL,14,Ffollowed by another in January 2026.
OL,16,FA typical household currently pays
OL,17,F#1,849 over 12 months, but if the
OL,18,Fprediction is correct, UK households
OL,19,Fcould pay #1,720 per year on average
OL,20,Ffrom July - that's a fall of #129 a
OL,21,Fyear.
