OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,FThe cap is based on per unit of
OL,7,Fenergy, not the whole bill, so if you
OL,8,Fuse more, you pay more.
OL,10,FWhy are energy prices falling?
OL,12,FMany factors will have contributed to
OL,13,Fthe price changes and will continue to
OL,14,Fshift the forecast.
OL,16,FCornwall Insight said prices are
OL,17,Faffected by "changing weather
OL,18,Fpatterns, the relaxation of EU gas
OL,19,Fstorage rules, ongoing debates around
OL,20,FUS tariffs and the continuing impact
OL,21,Fof the war in Ukraine."
