OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,FA drop in energy prices would be
OL,7,Fwelcomed by many households after
OL,8,Fprices remained high for a long period
OL,9,Fof time, but Cornwall Insight warned
OL,10,Fthat governments need to do more to
OL,11,Fsupport people as energy prices
OL,12,Ffluctuate.
OL,14,FDr Craig Lowrey, Principal Consultant
OL,15,Fat Cornwall Insight, warned that the
OL,16,Ffall in prices is a reminder of how
OL,17,Fvolatile the energy market remains.
