OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,F"If prices can go down, they can
OL,7,Fbounce back up, especially with the
OL,8,Funsettled global economic and
OL,9,Fpolitical landscape we are
OL,10,Fexperiencing," he said.
OL,12,F"This is not the moment for
OL,13,Fcomplacency. The government must
OL,14,Fcontinue to explore targeted support,
OL,15,Fincluding social tariffs, to ensure
OL,16,Fthose most in need are not left behind
OL,17,Fas the market evolves."
OL,19,FOfgem will release its updated energy
OL,20,Fprice cap for July on May 27.
