OL,3,CWhy your energy bills could fall this
OL,4,Csummer
OL,6,FDr Lowrey said: "The fall in the price
OL,7,Fcap is a welcome development and will
OL,8,Fbring much-needed breathing space for
OL,9,Fhouseholds after a prolonged period of
OL,10,Fhigh energy costs. It's a step in the
OL,11,Fright direction, but it should be
OL,12,Ftaken in context.
OL,14,F"Prices are falling, but not by enough
OL,15,Ffor the numerous households struggling
OL,16,Funder the weight of a cost-of-living
OL,17,Fcrisis, and bills remain well above
OL,18,Fthe levels seen at the start of the
OL,19,Fdecade. As such, there remains a risk
OL,20,Fthat energy will remain unaffordable
OL,21,Ffor many."
